# Runbook: Setting Up Preview Build Checks and Ephemeral PR Environments in Railway

This runbook guides engineers through configuring automated preview environments and commit build checks on Railway for non-production feature branches.

---

## Overview
By default, a Railway service binds directly to a single persistent target branch (such as `main`). To run continuous integration (CI) build checks and spin up temporary live previews for active development without manual reconfiguration, Railway utilizes **PR Environments**. 

When configured, opening a Pull Request (PR) on GitHub triggers an isolated, ephemeral replication of your target workspace infrastructure, ensuring all checks pass before code hits production.

---

## Step-by-Step Configuration

### Step 1: Access Global Project Settings
Do not search for this option inside the individual service properties. PR Environments are managed at the global infrastructure level.

1. Navigate to your **Railway Project Canvas**.
2. Locate the global **Project Settings** (represented by the **Gear Icon** ⚙️ or a dedicated Settings navigation link at the project dashboard level).

### Step 2: Enable PR Environments
1. Within Project Settings, locate and click on the **Environments** tab.
2. Scroll to the **PR Environments** section.
3. Toggle the feature to **Enabled**.
